6 PART I. CONFIDENTIALITY OF RECORDS
7 SECTION 1.1. G.S. 7B-2901(a) reads as rewritten:
8 "(a) The clerk shall maintain a complete record of all juvenile cases brought pursuant to
9 Subchapter I of this Chapter and filed in the clerk's office alleging abuse, neglect, or
10 dependency.office. The records shall be withheld from public inspection and, except as provided
11 in this subsection, may be examined only by order of the court. The record shall include the
12 summons, petition, custody order, court order, written motions, the electronic or mechanical
13 recording of the hearing, and other papers filed in the proceeding. The recording of the hearing
14 shall be reduced to a written transcript only when notice of appeal has been timely given. After
15 the time for appeal has expired with no appeal having been filed, the recording of the hearing
16 may be erased or destroyed upon the written order of the court or in accordance with a retention
17 schedule approved by the Director of the Administrative Office of the Courts and the Department
18 of Natural and Cultural Resources under G.S. 121‑5(c).
19 The following persons may examine the juvenile's record maintained pursuant to this
20 subsection and obtain copies of written parts of the record without an order of the court:
21 (1) The person named in the petition as the juvenile;juvenile, including the
22 juvenile who has reached the age of 18 or been emancipated, and their
23 attorney.
24 (2) The guardian ad litem;litem.
25 (3) The county department of social services; andservices and the Division of
26 Social Services of the Department of Health and Human Services.
27 (4) The juvenile's parent, guardian, or custodian, or the attorney for the juvenile
28 or the juvenile's parent, guardian, or custodian.Any named party in the action
29 and the attorney for any named party in the action."
30 SECTION 1.2. G.S. 50-13.2 reads as rewritten:
31 "§ 50-13.2. Who entitled to custody; terms of custody; visitation rights of grandparents;
32 taking child out of State; consideration of parent's military service.service;
33 confidentiality of court file and records.
34 …
