3 SECTION 3.3. G.S. 7B-903.1(c1) reads as rewritten:
4 "(c1) If juvenile siblings are removed from the home and placed in the nonsecure custody
5 of a county department of social services, the director shall make reasonable efforts to place the
6 juvenile siblings in the same home. The director is not required to make reasonable efforts under
7 this subsection if the director documents that placing the juvenile siblings would be contrary to
8 the safety or well‑being of any of the juvenile siblings. If, after making reasonable efforts, the
9 director is unable to place the juvenile siblings in the same home, the director shall make
10 reasonable efforts to provide frequent sibling visitation and ongoing interaction between the
11 juvenile siblings, unless the director documents that frequent visitation or other ongoing
12 interaction between the juvenile siblings would be contrary to the safety or well‑being of any of
13 the juvenile siblings."
