40 plan and secondary plan. Reunification shall be a primary or secondary plan unless the court
41 relieved the department of making reunification efforts at initial disposition under
42 G.S. 7B‑901(c), previously made written findings under G.S. 7B‑906.1(d)(3), the permanent plan
43 is or has been achieved, or the court makes written findings that reunification efforts clearly
44 would be unsuccessful or would be inconsistent with the juvenile's health or safety. The finding
45 that reunification efforts clearly would be unsuccessful or inconsistent with the juvenile's health
46 or safety may be made at any permanency planning hearing, and if made, shall eliminate
47 reunification as a plan. When reunification has been eliminated as a permanent plan, concurrent
48 planning is not required. Unless permanence has been achieved, the court shall order the county
49 department of social services to make efforts toward finalizing the primary and secondary
50 permanent plans or the sole permanent plan and may specify efforts that are reasonable to timely
51 achieve permanence for the juvenile."
