2 PART VIII. MOBILE COMMUNICATIONS PLATFORM
3 SECTION 8.1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative
4 Office of the Courts, Office of Indigent Services, the sum of two hundred and fifty thousand
5 dollars ($250,000) in recurring funds beginning in the 2026-2027 fiscal year to contract with an
6 approved vendor, no later than October 1, 2026, for the implementation of a secure, web and
7 mobile based communications platform for abuse, neglect, and dependency proceedings, and
8 termination of parental rights proceedings arising from those matters to ensure compliance with
9 federal and State requirements for the following:
10 (1) Advanced notification via automated electronic methods such as text
11 messaging or email to all parties and their attorneys, to the persons providing
12 care to the juvenile, and to any other person or agency designated by the court
13 for all court hearings and for interagency team meetings initiated by the
14 county department of social services such as permanency planning review
15 meetings, child and family team meetings, and placement status change
16 meetings.
17 (2) Enhanced communication between attorneys and clients and between parties
18 to reduce court continuances, share discovery, and reduce barriers to
19 permanency.
20 SECTION 8.2. The Administrative Office of the Courts, Indigent Services of NC ,
21 the Guardian Ad Litem Program, the North Carolina Division of Social Services (DSS), and any
22 other State or county agency or department necessary for implementation of the platform under
23 Section 10.1 of this act shall enter into a data sharing agreement to enable the selected vendor to
24 receive data necessary to ensure timely notification of court hearings and DSS initiated
25 interagency team meetings to all parties and their attorneys, the person providing care for the
26 juvenile, and any other necessary persons or agencies, and to ensure the communication platform
27 between the attorneys and clients and between parties receives the most accurate information
28 without redundant data entry.
29 SECTION 8.3. Section 8.1 of this act becomes effective on July 1, 2026.
30
